<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="R7-046" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7">
  <metadata>
    <title>Update AnalysisActionService to remove references to dropped fields</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <wave>4</wave>
    <estimated-effort>2-3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <tags>bff-api, code-impl, wave-4</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>044</dependencies>
    <fr-coverage>FR-03 + FR-04 (code cleanup portion)</fr-coverage>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Tasks 043 + 044 dropped `sprk_actiontypeid` and `sprk_executoractiontype` from `sprk_analysisaction`
    schema. `AnalysisActionService.cs` previously read these fields when materializing Action POCOs from
    Dataverse. With the fields gone, those reads will fail at runtime (Dataverse returns "attribute not
    found"). Find every reference to these two fields in `AnalysisActionService.cs` (and anywhere else
    in `src/server/`) and remove them. Simplify the Action read path per spec affected-areas note:
    "Action read path simplifies (no ActionType from lookup)".
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET backend developer simplifying a Dataverse read service. Goal: AnalysisActionService no
    longer reads dropped fields; build green; tests green. Mirror task 042's cascade-deletion discipline:
    remove the read; remove any private helper / mapping logic that becomes unused; verify build at each step.
  </role>

  <goal>
    1. Grep `src/server/` for `sprk_actiontypeid` + `sprk_executoractiontype` — should hit `AnalysisActionService.cs` (plus possibly DTOs, mapping code, tests)
    2. Every read of those fields removed from `AnalysisActionService.cs`
    3. Any DTO properties bound to those columns removed (cascade — if no other consumer)
    4. Any column-selection lists ("Cols" / `$select=…`) that name those fields updated to omit them
    5. Tests for `AnalysisActionService` updated to remove fixture setups for those fields
    6. `dotnet build` passes; `dotnet test` passes
    7. Post-task grep for both field names returns ZERO hits in `src/server/` + `tests/`
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="design-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/plan.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="cleanup-target">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/AnalysisActionService.cs</file>
    <file purpose="possible-cleanup-target">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Models/ (DTOs that bind sprk_analysisaction fields)</file>
    <file purpose="bff-constraints">.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
    <file purpose="prior-tasks">043-drop-sprk-actiontypeid-lookup.poml, 044-drop-sprk-executoractiontype-int.poml (cite for traceability)</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec FR-03 acceptance">Field removed from Dataverse; Action read path (AnalysisActionService) no longer references it.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-04 acceptance">Field removed; no code reads it.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec affected-areas">`AnalysisActionService.cs` — Action read path simplifies (no ActionType from lookup).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">BFF AI Architecture — Action represents prompt template + schema + temperature only (post-R7). Dispatch lives on node, not on Action.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">BFF Publish Hygiene — verify publish-size delta (expected: small NEGATIVE; modest dead-code removal).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-038">Testing Strategy — fixture cleanup MUST happen with code change (no "deferred test update"). Tests don't gain new mocks; they shrink to match the simpler service.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §11">No new component. Cleanup of existing service. Justification rule does not apply.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md §F.6">Test-update obligation — caller test updates MUST happen with code change, not deferred.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>ai/bff-architecture</topic>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-013-bff-ai-architecture.md</file>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-029-bff-publish-hygiene.md</file>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-038-testing-strategy.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Cascade-deletion discipline" location="task 042 POML">
        Delete reads → build → identify unused helpers/DTOs → delete → repeat until build clean.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Dataverse $select column-list trimming" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/AnalysisActionService.cs">
        Many read services maintain explicit "Cols" arrays for $select. Trim the dropped field names from these arrays.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      With schema dropped (tasks 043 + 044), reading the dropped fields would 404 at runtime. This task
      mops up `AnalysisActionService.cs` and any related DTO/mapping code so the build represents the
      post-FR-03 + FR-04 reality. The Action POCO becomes simpler: just prompt template + schema +
      temperature (per spec's Action-as-prompt-template framing).
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="044" status="must-complete-first">Schema-cascade pair complete. Both fields dropped. Reading them would fail.</dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>Task 042 deleted the largest reader (`ExecuteAnalysisAsync`) of these fields; remaining reads concentrate in `AnalysisActionService`.</item>
      <item>Task 045 documents the lookup table as decorative — note may inform commit message framing.</item>
      <item>Task 047 cumulative wave publish-size check follows immediately.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Rigor Declaration">
      Output: 🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL · 📋 REASON: code-impl in BFF (.cs file modification, tag bff-api+code-impl, ADR-013+029+038 applicable) — quality gates Step 9.5 required · Proceeding with Step 0...
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Load context">
      Read project CLAUDE.md + spec.md FR-03 + FR-04 + plan.md Wave 4 + .claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md + AnalysisActionService.cs.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Verify prerequisite">
      Confirm tasks 043 + 044 marked ✅ in TASK-INDEX. If either is incomplete, STOP and report — runtime schema is not yet in the post-deletion state.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Grep dropped field names — production code">
      Run: Grep pattern="(sprk_actiontypeid|sprk_executoractiontype)" glob="**/*.cs" output_mode="content" -n true
      Capture every hit (file + line + surrounding code). Expected: AnalysisActionService.cs + possibly DTOs + tests.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Read AnalysisActionService.cs in full">
      Identify: where the fields are read in $select / column lists, where they are bound to DTOs, where they are projected to Action POCOs. Track the cascade.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Remove dropped-field reads + cascade DTO/mapping">
      For each grep hit in production code:
      - Remove from $select / column-list array
      - Remove from DTO bindings
      - Remove any private helper that consumed only the dropped field
      - Simplify Action POCO if either dropped field had a property exposed on it
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Build — first sweep">
      Run: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`
      Capture compiler warnings about newly-unused members. Cascade through deletes until build is clean.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Update tests">
      Find tests for `AnalysisActionService` and any DTO classes touched. Remove fixture setups for dropped fields. Per ADR-038: no new mocks; tests shrink (no DI-registration tests, no ctor null-check tests added).
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Build + run tests">
      Run: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`
      Run: `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/`
      Goal: 0 errors, 0 NEW warnings, all tests pass.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Verify grep state">
      Run: Grep pattern="(sprk_actiontypeid|sprk_executoractiontype)" glob="**/*.cs"
      Required: ZERO hits in `src/server/` + `tests/`. Pre-existing historical references in COMMIT MESSAGES are NOT in scope (untracked by this grep).
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `/code-review` on modified files. Run `/adr-check` against ADR-013 + ADR-029 + ADR-038 + bff-extensions.md.
      Fix any findings before commit.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Publish + size check (running tally toward task 047)">
      Run: dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish-task046/
      Measure compressed size. Expected: small NEGATIVE delta.
    </step>
    <step order="11" name="Update current-task.md + TASK-INDEX">
      Mark task 046 status complete; advance current-task.md to task 047.
    </step>
    <step order="12" name="Commit">
      Commit cleanup + test updates with conventional message.
      Example: refactor(bff/r7): drop AnalysisActionService refs to deleted Action fields (Wave 4 task 046, FR-03+FR-04)
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool>Read (AnalysisActionService.cs + DTOs + tests)</tool>
    <tool>Grep (dropped field names — pre + post)</tool>
    <tool>Edit (cleanup of reads + cascade)</tool>
